WEBVTT

00:01.871 --> 00:03.612
JEROME:
Then you shall hear in heaven

00:03.699 --> 00:06.223
the place of your dwelling,
their plea, and you shall

00:06.310 --> 00:07.616
vindicate them.

00:07.703 --> 00:09.748
Previously onBarkskins...

00:09.835 --> 00:12.751
[shouting, grunting]

00:12.838 --> 00:16.320
We will have
a proper wedding ceremony.

00:16.407 --> 00:18.540
You brought your child bride
to our Doma.

00:18.627 --> 00:20.107
I'm leaving this place.

00:20.194 --> 00:22.196
There is a surplus
of stray men in Wobik.

00:22.283 --> 00:23.762
I am sure there will soon be

00:23.849 --> 00:25.503
a long line of suitors
at the inn.

00:25.590 --> 00:26.809
It will be good for business.

00:26.896 --> 00:27.984
Look upon Alice.

00:28.071 --> 00:29.725
Her kind and beautiful face.

00:29.812 --> 00:31.205
Her eyes.

00:31.292 --> 00:33.381
Cold, black stones.

00:33.468 --> 00:35.948
I would like to know
why you neglected to tell

00:36.036 --> 00:38.212
the Hudson's Bay man
about the pistols.

00:38.299 --> 00:40.344
YVON:
Captain Wale said
you were to deliver something.

00:40.431 --> 00:41.345
Pistols.

00:41.432 --> 00:42.651
A barrelful.

00:42.738 --> 00:44.348
They were to arm the Iroquois

00:44.435 --> 00:45.741
so that they could use them
against the French.

00:45.828 --> 00:48.048
Where are they?

00:51.138 --> 00:53.096
[church bell tolling]

01:01.626 --> 01:03.802
-[music playing in distance]
-[indistinct chatter]

01:03.889 --> 01:06.022
I must thank you, Mother.

01:25.389 --> 01:27.391
[music, laughter, chatter
continuing in distance]

01:29.915 --> 01:31.917
[horse whinnies]

01:59.728 --> 02:02.122
I apologize.

02:02.209 --> 02:03.993
It was not my intention
to scare you.

02:05.212 --> 02:08.084
It's a, uh, beautiful night.

02:08.171 --> 02:11.827
Yes, it is.

02:11.914 --> 02:13.872
Though it is cold.

02:13.959 --> 02:16.658
Yes, well, autumn
has a proselytizing hand

02:16.745 --> 02:18.181
over the landscape,

02:18.268 --> 02:21.445
leaving golden leaves
at its touch.

02:23.839 --> 02:25.797
Um...

02:25.884 --> 02:27.799
Did you know that, uh,

02:27.886 --> 02:29.061
just the other day,

02:29.149 --> 02:31.716
I purchased
six albino beaver pelts?

02:33.109 --> 02:35.198
Would you like to see them?

02:36.330 --> 02:37.853
Yes.

02:37.940 --> 02:39.202
I would.

02:39.289 --> 02:41.073
Good. Good.

02:41.161 --> 02:44.076
Then I will show them to you.

02:44.164 --> 02:46.818
I also purchased
some, uh, spice

02:46.905 --> 02:48.298
by the name of nutmeg.

02:48.385 --> 02:50.561
Came to me in a barrel

02:50.648 --> 02:52.781
from the Island of Rum.

02:55.131 --> 02:57.873
I can still smell it
in my beard.

03:01.920 --> 03:04.619
Well, I...

03:04.706 --> 03:07.404
bid you good evening.

03:15.282 --> 03:16.979
[chuckles softly]

03:20.722 --> 03:22.332
♪ ♪

03:48.358 --> 03:49.707
♪ ♪

03:49.794 --> 03:52.144
[door opens]

03:53.450 --> 03:55.278
[door closes]

03:55.365 --> 03:57.324
[footsteps departing]

03:59.456 --> 04:01.415
♪ ♪

04:05.462 --> 04:07.421
[indistinct chatter]

04:23.611 --> 04:25.830
[inhales deeply]

04:28.659 --> 04:30.095
-[chuckles softly]
-I have some eggs,
if you would like.

04:30.182 --> 04:33.534
No. No.

04:33.621 --> 04:36.537
The stew is all I require.

04:36.624 --> 04:39.888
-MATHILDE: Mm.
-Out there, among the savages,

04:39.975 --> 04:42.499
it was this stew
I thought about.

04:42.586 --> 04:44.893
The Jesuits had their Bibles.

04:44.980 --> 04:47.939
But I had this.

04:49.941 --> 04:51.421
Blasphemous.

04:51.508 --> 04:54.119
No. It is not blasphemous.

04:54.206 --> 04:57.209
It is the simple things that
bind us to this world, Captain.

04:57.297 --> 04:59.124
No.

04:59.211 --> 05:01.344
Sit.

05:03.825 --> 05:07.611
I would like to take a moment

05:07.698 --> 05:11.398
before it is time
to face my vicious tasks today.

05:11.485 --> 05:13.443
I suppose.

05:23.323 --> 05:25.237
[short chuckle]

05:26.761 --> 05:29.894
That is the right medicine.

05:29.981 --> 05:31.548
I am whole again.

05:31.635 --> 05:33.724
Mmm.

05:33.811 --> 05:36.727
Mmm.
[chuckles softly]

05:38.860 --> 05:39.991
No, no.

05:40.078 --> 05:41.950
I am fine. I am fine.

05:42.037 --> 05:43.212
Go back to your chores.

05:48.260 --> 05:50.872
Has she found her tongue yet?

05:50.959 --> 05:54.049
Not as of yet. Simple words.

05:54.136 --> 05:56.094
Hmm.

05:56.181 --> 05:59.533
She saw the horrors
of the Iroquois, no doubt.

06:01.317 --> 06:03.493
-Did you see the rest
of the Iroquois?
-No.

06:03.580 --> 06:06.104
Only Trepagny's man did.

06:06.191 --> 06:08.498
But I don't need to see them
to know they're out there,

06:08.585 --> 06:10.021
stalking about,

06:10.108 --> 06:12.241
hatching plans

06:12.328 --> 06:14.678
with an Englishman at the helm.

06:16.985 --> 06:18.160
Ah.

06:20.292 --> 06:21.468
Hmm.

06:24.862 --> 06:27.778
I was wondering...
[clears throat]

06:27.865 --> 06:30.955
when I have settled
this Iroquois matter...

06:31.042 --> 06:33.523
[clears throat]
that you and I, we...

06:33.610 --> 06:35.569
might go for a stroll?

06:37.484 --> 06:39.442
-A stroll?
-Mm.

06:39.529 --> 06:43.359
There is a hill just beyond
the walls with a view.

06:43.446 --> 06:46.014
We could take in
the fall colors.

06:48.495 --> 06:50.932
Pardon me if I am
being too forward.

06:55.110 --> 06:56.981
No, Captain.

06:57.068 --> 06:59.419
I would like that very much.

07:01.333 --> 07:02.770
[door opens]

07:09.994 --> 07:13.389
One only has to
say the word "English,"

07:13.476 --> 07:14.782
and they come running

07:14.869 --> 07:17.262
like sick black dogs

07:17.349 --> 07:18.916
at low tide.

07:19.003 --> 07:21.789
Captain.

07:21.876 --> 07:25.183
I heard about
your selfless heroics

07:25.270 --> 07:28.056
with the Iroquois and
the tragedy with the priests.

07:32.626 --> 07:34.715
Well, I suppose
there is nothing more

07:34.802 --> 07:36.543
that needs be said
on the subject.

07:36.630 --> 07:39.589
Silence will suffice, then.

07:44.986 --> 07:46.422
Good day.

07:55.126 --> 07:57.259
Might I have a word, Mathilde?

07:59.914 --> 08:02.873
-Perhaps the kitchen is best.
-Of course.

08:12.361 --> 08:14.232
I wish to make you
a proposition.

08:14.319 --> 08:16.278
Go on.

08:16.365 --> 08:18.715
I should like you make use
of your stables.

08:18.802 --> 08:20.282
I have an excess of barrels.

08:20.369 --> 08:22.066
Trade having slowed
due to the recent unrest.

08:22.153 --> 08:25.330
I'm prepared to pay you
handsomely.

08:29.857 --> 08:32.947
You can store them
free of charge.

08:33.034 --> 08:35.950
No. I insist.
I will pay.

08:36.037 --> 08:38.648
[scoffs]
Yes, a few coins.

08:38.735 --> 08:41.651
But that is not the only reason
you are here.

08:43.740 --> 08:46.134
-It is.
-Oh.

08:46.221 --> 08:48.658
Then it is a shame,
because there is a greater deal

08:48.745 --> 08:51.095
to be made besides
storing a few barrels

08:51.182 --> 08:53.315
in my stables
for some few coins.

08:53.402 --> 08:55.709
Well, only a fool would refuse
to entertain a greater deal.

08:55.796 --> 08:57.449
Go on.

08:59.582 --> 09:01.889
Go on, Renardette.
I am fine.

09:03.630 --> 09:05.588
You wish to restore
your standing in this town.

09:05.675 --> 09:07.416
Am I right?

09:07.503 --> 09:10.027
-I shall recover my good name.
-Barrels and trade

09:10.114 --> 09:12.856
do not remove the stain
of your English name.

09:12.943 --> 09:14.902
They have before.

09:14.989 --> 09:17.078
Those times are gone.

09:17.165 --> 09:18.732
You overstepped, Mr. Cooke.

09:18.819 --> 09:20.821
Only a... a stubborn man

09:20.908 --> 09:24.738
would walk upon a frozen lake
when the sun is shining.

09:24.825 --> 09:28.306
-We can help each other.
-And how is that?

09:30.308 --> 09:32.484
I believe, uh,

09:32.572 --> 09:35.705
Delphine has caught your eye?

09:38.882 --> 09:41.363
Uh, I don't know
what you're talking about.

09:41.450 --> 09:43.104
Come now, Mr. Cooke.

09:43.191 --> 09:45.106
I have seen it with my own eyes.

09:45.193 --> 09:47.499
There is no shame
in looking upon her beauty.

09:47.587 --> 09:49.153
It is there for all to see.

09:49.240 --> 09:52.113
Now then, it would be prudent

09:52.200 --> 09:54.376
for you to make
a match with her.

09:54.463 --> 09:56.639
And in return,

09:56.726 --> 09:58.815
you will help me expand the inn.

10:00.991 --> 10:03.603
Mathilde, I came here

10:03.690 --> 10:06.127
merely to store excess barrels.

10:06.214 --> 10:08.912
And if you agree to my terms,

10:08.999 --> 10:11.785
you will leave
with a French wife.

10:15.527 --> 10:17.486
All right, then, we shall agree

10:17.573 --> 10:19.836
to the storage of the barrels.

10:19.923 --> 10:21.577
Think on it if you must,

10:21.664 --> 10:23.927
but you will
come to the same place.

10:24.014 --> 10:26.147
[door opens]

10:28.410 --> 10:32.153
My orders were to deliver
the pistols to Bill Selby.

10:32.240 --> 10:35.156
And then Selby would
arm the Iroquois.

10:35.243 --> 10:37.724
Step back and take
the trade as it comes.

10:38.942 --> 10:40.901
But the result is the same.

10:42.424 --> 10:44.687
When I saw what they did
at the settlement...

10:46.428 --> 10:47.777
What I did...

10:47.864 --> 10:49.387
We've heard your account.

10:49.474 --> 10:51.476
I haven't told you everything.

10:52.564 --> 10:53.783
The girl.

10:54.958 --> 10:56.264
The one at the inn.

10:56.351 --> 10:59.789
Yes, she smiled.
An odd detail.

10:59.876 --> 11:01.225
No.

11:01.312 --> 11:04.533
I saw her slit a man's throat.

11:04.620 --> 11:07.536
We saw each other,
carried up in the madness.

11:09.016 --> 11:11.583
The same will happen to you.

11:30.646 --> 11:33.823
-If it's another body...
-No.

11:33.910 --> 11:36.565
It's the pistols.

11:36.652 --> 11:39.220
I put them in the river.

11:39.307 --> 11:41.091
A barrelful.

11:41.178 --> 11:43.964
-The ones Cooke gave you?
-Yes.

11:44.051 --> 11:47.794
And now my business
with the Company is concluded.

11:47.881 --> 11:51.493
I have been found.
You have my account.

11:58.021 --> 12:00.632
This is a waste of our time.

12:12.732 --> 12:14.864
BOUCHARD:
No.

12:14.951 --> 12:16.910
No, no, no, no.

12:16.997 --> 12:19.477
Monsieur Sel was
the lucky one. Hmm?

12:19.564 --> 12:21.610
Though the savages
left their mark.

12:21.697 --> 12:23.481
-Show them.
-[grunts]

12:24.569 --> 12:25.832
That's enough.

12:25.919 --> 12:27.442
TREPAGNY:
It is the Englishman

12:27.529 --> 12:30.271
Bill Selby
we should be worried about.

12:30.358 --> 12:33.187
Yes. And he is tied
to the Hudson Bay Company.

12:33.274 --> 12:36.451
He will stir the whole region
with his wand of violence.

12:36.538 --> 12:38.714
That is why you will help us
deal with him.

12:38.801 --> 12:41.412
Oh.
Well, you asked us

12:41.499 --> 12:43.240
to entreat the Iroquois,

12:43.327 --> 12:45.852
and now there are
three dead priests.

12:45.939 --> 12:48.680
We all serve the king,
Monsieur Trepagny. Even you.

12:48.768 --> 12:50.421
We are far from the king.

12:50.508 --> 12:52.467
It is war
we are looking to avoid.

12:52.554 --> 12:55.252
That is why we should send
for soldiers from Quebec City.

12:55.339 --> 12:56.950
Run straight at the Iroquois.

12:57.037 --> 12:58.865
Put them in the dirt!

12:58.952 --> 13:00.431
And the Wendat, too.

13:00.518 --> 13:02.999
Bouchard.
The Wendat are no part of this.

13:03.086 --> 13:05.480
If Wobik falls,
your precious Doma will be next.

13:05.567 --> 13:07.003
My Doma will be fine.
I will leave you

13:07.090 --> 13:09.310
to chart your own course
for Wobik.

13:09.397 --> 13:12.052
Captain, you will lead
a recovery party in the morning.

13:12.139 --> 13:13.793
Two soldiers will accompany you.

13:13.880 --> 13:16.534
You will bring back the bodies
of Father Jerome,

13:16.621 --> 13:17.579
Father Gabriel and Father Clape.

13:17.666 --> 13:19.189
If I may speak...

13:19.276 --> 13:22.149
the Englishman
wants us to come for them.

13:22.236 --> 13:23.498
It's a trap.

13:29.069 --> 13:31.767
All right.

13:31.854 --> 13:34.161
They want French...

13:34.248 --> 13:37.860
but we send an Englishman.

13:37.947 --> 13:41.211
Send Mr. Cooke.
Huh?

13:41.298 --> 13:43.866
Let him prove his loyalty
to Wobik.

13:45.781 --> 13:47.348
[whispers]:
It is a very bright idea.

13:52.788 --> 13:54.790
Bring Elisha Cooke to us.

13:54.877 --> 13:58.185
That is the clever play,
your eminence.

14:00.274 --> 14:02.842
We will accompany Mr. Cooke.

14:02.929 --> 14:05.496
The light of the Lord
shall shield us.

14:05.583 --> 14:08.325
Those savages will slaughter
nuns the same as priests.

14:08.412 --> 14:10.937
We have been among the Iroquois.

14:11.024 --> 14:12.721
Healed their wounded, even.

14:13.809 --> 14:16.029
We will bring the dead back.

14:18.770 --> 14:21.338
I will return with Mr. Cooke.

14:23.253 --> 14:26.343
[door opens, closes]

14:26.430 --> 14:29.781
I am anxious
to return to the Doma.

14:29.869 --> 14:32.915
If the Iroquois come, these
walls and a few men with muskets

14:33.002 --> 14:34.395
will not stop them.

14:34.482 --> 14:36.745
I have seen entire towns
put to the torch.

14:38.703 --> 14:40.836
Even so, I will stay
another night in the inn.

14:40.923 --> 14:42.403
We will make haste.

14:42.490 --> 14:45.449
We have a wedding celebration
to plan.

14:45.536 --> 14:47.190
We can get married in the inn.

14:47.277 --> 14:50.019
I can be measured
for my wedding dress.

14:50.106 --> 14:51.934
Mathilde can prepare the feast.

14:52.021 --> 14:53.936
The celebration
will be at the Doma,

14:54.023 --> 14:55.895
-[scoffs]
-and Mathilde can prepare
a feast there,

14:55.982 --> 14:57.809
if she agrees.

14:57.897 --> 14:59.463
The Doma will be fine.

14:59.550 --> 15:01.291
Mari is gone.

15:04.077 --> 15:05.992
Your son, too.

15:06.079 --> 15:07.689
She told me of the dead ram.

15:07.776 --> 15:09.473
She said it spoke of your end.

15:09.560 --> 15:11.214
One more night in Wobik,

15:11.301 --> 15:13.477
and we will know more
of the Iroquois.

15:13.564 --> 15:16.916
We don't wish to make
Mari's silly words come true.

15:23.487 --> 15:24.924
One more night.

15:29.276 --> 15:31.887
Yes. Come.

16:01.699 --> 16:03.092
Clan Mother.

16:03.179 --> 16:05.703
There is no place for you here.

16:05.790 --> 16:08.315
You chose Trepagny.

16:08.402 --> 16:10.186
You lived in his house.

16:10.273 --> 16:13.146
-Bore him a son.
-Please.

16:13.233 --> 16:14.321
Would you have us
go into the woods?

16:16.410 --> 16:19.239
Let me show you
what Trepagny has done.

16:43.176 --> 16:46.527
He died defending Trepagny
against the Iroquois.

16:47.963 --> 16:51.010
There was an Englishman
with the Iroquois.

16:51.097 --> 16:53.055
They have allied again.

16:53.142 --> 16:54.883
Either the English
are using the Iroquois

16:54.970 --> 16:56.319
or the Iroquois
are using the English.

16:56.406 --> 16:57.799
It is bad for us all.

17:03.761 --> 17:05.676
GAY BILL:
"It is easier to find men

17:05.763 --> 17:07.678
"who will volunteer to die

17:07.765 --> 17:09.854
"than those who are willing

17:09.941 --> 17:12.857
to endure pain with patience."

17:15.164 --> 17:17.384
Julius Caesar.

17:18.689 --> 17:21.605
But then, you don't even know

17:21.692 --> 17:23.607
what a Roman is or a general, so

17:23.694 --> 17:26.958
I guess these words
mean shit-all to you, Chief.

17:27.046 --> 17:30.571
There's only one word
that matters here.

17:30.658 --> 17:32.529
-French.
-When will they come?

17:32.616 --> 17:33.748
Soon.

17:33.835 --> 17:35.358
And the pistols you promised?

17:35.445 --> 17:37.447
They're coming.

17:37.534 --> 17:39.667
But...

17:39.754 --> 17:42.844
as a matter of goodwill...

17:44.411 --> 17:47.283
take mine.

17:49.024 --> 17:52.723
In the meantime,
let's keep the mutilating

17:52.810 --> 17:55.248
of the Jesuit sorcerers
to a minimum.

17:58.816 --> 18:00.470
The dogs, too.

18:02.037 --> 18:03.821
We want the French
to feel they've at least

18:03.908 --> 18:06.041
got something
to put in the ground.

18:18.445 --> 18:20.534
Stop.

18:20.621 --> 18:22.449
-MAN: In the back?
-Yes, in the back.

18:24.842 --> 18:26.583
Bring it here, Charles.

18:29.543 --> 18:31.327
Secure that one over there.

18:31.414 --> 18:33.503
Is there something of value
in it?

18:33.590 --> 18:34.852
You don't need to know
what's in them.

18:34.939 --> 18:36.115
Just put it there.

18:37.246 --> 18:39.074
Through here.

18:39.161 --> 18:41.120
-To the back.
-BOUCHARD: Cooke!

18:53.219 --> 18:56.047
You will be the one to go there.

18:56.135 --> 18:58.572
COOKE:
Intendant, you must
see the unfairness of it.

18:58.659 --> 19:00.530
RENE:
Charles?

19:05.448 --> 19:07.058
You look well.

19:11.802 --> 19:13.239
I looked for you.

19:13.326 --> 19:15.589
After you ran off.

19:20.071 --> 19:21.986
I vouched for you with Trepagny.

19:22.073 --> 19:24.685
-And now I owe you a debt?
-No.

19:24.772 --> 19:27.688
Then why recount
what has already passed?

19:27.775 --> 19:29.646
I am no longer
pledged to Trepagny.

19:29.733 --> 19:30.908
That is your fate.

19:30.995 --> 19:33.389
You seem born to it.

19:33.476 --> 19:35.696
May you get land
and then grow old keeping it.

19:36.871 --> 19:39.090
-And you?
-I have been

19:39.178 --> 19:40.701
taken on
by a successful merchant,

19:40.788 --> 19:44.444
Mr. Cooke.
I've already begun to prosper.

19:48.448 --> 19:50.841
Yes.

19:53.583 --> 19:55.542
Of course.

19:55.629 --> 19:58.849
I see now who you are.

19:58.936 --> 20:01.243
I'm who I have always been.

20:01.330 --> 20:04.203
As are you, I suppose.

20:04.290 --> 20:07.031
Good luck, Rene.

20:16.040 --> 20:19.783
I must, uh, have a word
with my man.

20:19.870 --> 20:22.133
Be quick about it.

20:32.666 --> 20:34.842
COOKE:
You will come with me.
I need your assistance.

20:34.929 --> 20:36.365
What for?

20:38.759 --> 20:42.241
I have been tasked
with retrieving the bodies

20:42.328 --> 20:45.200
of the priests and Deputy Guy.

20:45.287 --> 20:47.724
If I do not, I am afraid that

20:47.811 --> 20:50.118
they will hang me
from the palisades.

20:50.205 --> 20:52.773
With respect, sir,
this has nothing to do with me.

20:54.862 --> 20:56.429
You will have nothing

20:56.516 --> 20:58.387
if I am killed.
You will have nothing.

20:58.474 --> 20:59.997
Do you understand that?

21:00.084 --> 21:01.825
You will come with me
or you will be back

21:01.912 --> 21:04.001
outside the walls,
fending for yourself.

21:04.088 --> 21:05.481
BOUCHARD:
What's this?

21:05.568 --> 21:07.396
Uh, nothing.
My, uh,

21:07.483 --> 21:09.659
my man will accompany me,

21:09.746 --> 21:12.488
and, uh, he will-will
be of much assistance.

21:12.575 --> 21:15.143
-This better not be some sort
of trick, Cooke.
-No trick.

21:15.230 --> 21:16.840
Another set of hands.
His addition will, uh,

21:16.927 --> 21:18.277
speed our return.

21:18.364 --> 21:20.235
All right.

21:20.322 --> 21:22.324
But if he is killed
by the Iroquois,

21:22.411 --> 21:23.847
his body will be for the ravens.

21:23.934 --> 21:25.327
Very well, very well.

21:25.414 --> 21:27.460
-We must gather our supplies.
-Uh-huh.

21:27.547 --> 21:30.071
[chuckles]
Gather all the lucky trinkets

21:30.158 --> 21:31.812
you have, Cooke.

21:38.035 --> 21:40.560
I'll be waiting at the gate.

21:41.735 --> 21:44.085
Provisions for your journey.

21:46.130 --> 21:48.307
Thank you.

21:48.394 --> 21:49.873
Lavender.

21:51.397 --> 21:54.095
It's very kind of you, Delphine.

22:06.325 --> 22:08.718
Prove your worth, English.
[chuckles]

22:08.805 --> 22:11.242
Or die trying.

22:19.642 --> 22:21.078
Follow smartly.

22:24.299 --> 22:26.388
This new one in your house,

22:26.475 --> 22:28.216
she's French?

22:28.303 --> 22:30.261
Yes.

22:30.349 --> 22:32.481
You are still Wendat.

22:32.568 --> 22:35.702
She should be no match for you.
Go.

22:35.789 --> 22:37.530
Leave Theo with us.

22:37.617 --> 22:40.315
Fight for your place
with Trepagny.

22:46.582 --> 22:49.063
[crickets chirping]

22:55.591 --> 22:57.680
SABRINE:
There is food, if you like.

22:59.595 --> 23:01.902
Thank you, Mother, but I've lost
even the thought of food.

23:11.433 --> 23:13.217
You are afraid?

23:13.304 --> 23:16.090
Any right-minded man would be.

23:16.177 --> 23:19.006
I am not a man,
but if it is any solace,

23:19.093 --> 23:22.705
I have prayed and reflected
on your position.

23:22.792 --> 23:26.448
And I do not believe God intends
to punish you, Mr. Cooke.

23:26.535 --> 23:28.058
Well, that's a relief.

23:28.145 --> 23:30.713
Do you have any other messages
from above?

23:30.800 --> 23:32.933
No.

23:33.020 --> 23:35.762
But I have spoken
with the soldiers,

23:35.849 --> 23:37.938
and I would like your assurance
that we approach

23:38.025 --> 23:40.636
the retrieval of the bodies
peacefully.

23:40.723 --> 23:42.421
COOKE:
And how would you suggest
we do that

23:42.508 --> 23:45.424
if there are Iroquois about,
as there most assuredly will be?

23:45.511 --> 23:47.338
I will reason with them.

23:47.426 --> 23:49.602
If we are to avoid
an all-out war,

23:49.689 --> 23:51.691
it must start here.

23:53.475 --> 23:56.652
And I shall
follow your lead, Mother.

23:59.612 --> 24:01.570
[sighs]

24:02.789 --> 24:04.355
[coughs]

24:04.443 --> 24:06.270
[sniffles]

24:14.714 --> 24:17.934
My sister will expect
full account.

24:18.021 --> 24:21.416
I have laid down
the events for you.

24:23.070 --> 24:25.768
They put your absence
in a favorable light.

24:41.958 --> 24:44.265
I'd like some air.

24:44.352 --> 24:46.528
-Beans will be ready soon.
-I will be back

24:46.615 --> 24:48.312
for the beans.
I, uh...

24:48.399 --> 24:51.011
want some time to reflect.

24:58.148 --> 25:00.455
He killed those people
for the Company.

25:01.978 --> 25:03.937
They'll ask us to do the same.

25:04.024 --> 25:06.505
Arming the Iroquois.

25:06.592 --> 25:09.682
He will not be the same man
your sister knew.

25:11.205 --> 25:13.207
Not after what he's done.

25:14.687 --> 25:17.385
Every man
faces his sins in the end.

25:18.473 --> 25:20.562
I don't believe that.

25:42.105 --> 25:44.717
♪ ♪

26:03.213 --> 26:05.389
You'd shoot me in the back?

26:05.476 --> 26:07.043
[scoffs]

26:07.130 --> 26:09.089
That's the Company way.

26:11.265 --> 26:14.094
No, it is not.

26:14.181 --> 26:17.663
-You left this.
-Let me go.

26:17.750 --> 26:19.447
I'll walk into the woods
and begone.

26:19.534 --> 26:21.971
You will do as a man
and face your responsibilities.

26:22.058 --> 26:24.017
I am no man.

26:24.104 --> 26:27.107
Or I'd kill you and stop
what you're about to do.

26:28.674 --> 26:30.937
You've lost your mind, Randall.

26:31.024 --> 26:32.939
[laughs]

26:33.026 --> 26:36.812
No, it's the opposite.

26:36.899 --> 26:39.032
You should get out now.

26:39.119 --> 26:40.990
Leave your posting
in the Company.

26:41.077 --> 26:42.688
Why would I do that?

26:44.037 --> 26:45.429
'Cause you'll end up like me.

26:47.127 --> 26:50.347
Come back to the fire,
and we'll eat beans.

26:52.088 --> 26:54.700
The woods are full
of men like you.

27:10.019 --> 27:12.195
[grunts]

27:23.903 --> 27:25.861
♪ ♪

27:51.321 --> 27:53.715
♪ ♪

28:21.743 --> 28:23.702
♪ ♪

28:48.422 --> 28:50.163
[birds chirping]

29:03.524 --> 29:05.744
I will start back to work
on the sky table.

29:29.028 --> 29:31.334
You see?

29:31.421 --> 29:34.033
Everything is fine,
just as we left it.

29:34.120 --> 29:36.818
No Iroquois.

29:38.124 --> 29:40.082
I am a lady.

29:40.169 --> 29:43.477
Not some Indian who will cook
and clean for you.

29:43.564 --> 29:46.654
We will speak no more of Mari.

29:46.741 --> 29:48.699
MELISSANDE:
Do you miss her?

29:50.745 --> 29:52.747
No.

29:54.793 --> 29:57.012
We will make do.

29:57.099 --> 29:59.145
I will not be abandoned again.

30:02.017 --> 30:03.453
Yes, of course.

30:06.630 --> 30:08.545
Now put the fire to blaze

30:08.632 --> 30:10.983
and see about some food.

30:34.093 --> 30:36.660
[grunting]

30:43.711 --> 30:45.278
Mari.

30:57.594 --> 30:59.683
Trepagny believes you've left.

30:59.770 --> 31:01.511
I did.

31:01.598 --> 31:03.209
And now I am back.

31:03.296 --> 31:05.385
Theo?

31:05.472 --> 31:07.300
He's with my people.

31:07.387 --> 31:09.693
It is good for him.

31:09.780 --> 31:13.175
Did Melissande
return with Trepagny?

31:16.439 --> 31:18.441
Tell me.

31:20.879 --> 31:21.923
Yes.

31:23.533 --> 31:25.579
They are planning
a wedding celebration.

31:28.060 --> 31:30.714
Perhaps it's better
you stay away.

31:31.890 --> 31:33.282
I'm going back to my cabin.

31:33.369 --> 31:35.850
I will make an early supper,

31:35.937 --> 31:38.113
and you are welcome
to join me if you wish.

31:40.463 --> 31:42.465
I won't.

32:08.448 --> 32:09.623
Renardette.

32:09.710 --> 32:11.930
That man, Mr. Cross.

32:13.105 --> 32:14.628
Did he hurt you?

32:14.715 --> 32:16.717
No.

32:18.023 --> 32:20.416
But you saw him?

32:23.115 --> 32:24.246
Yes.

32:24.333 --> 32:27.249
He was out there,

32:27.336 --> 32:30.078
when the Iroquois
killed those families?

32:31.558 --> 32:33.734
Where is your family?

32:47.095 --> 32:49.010
Come.
I have a job for you.

32:54.407 --> 32:57.976
I need you to keep a keen eye

32:58.063 --> 33:00.587
on Mr. Cooke's barrels.

33:00.674 --> 33:02.806
Can you do that?

33:02.893 --> 33:06.245
Yes.

33:06.332 --> 33:08.595
He has entrusted them to me,

33:08.682 --> 33:10.901
and I will
have that trust returned.

33:10.989 --> 33:14.209
I will watch.

33:14.296 --> 33:17.169
A close watch.

33:23.784 --> 33:25.873
And I will get you

33:25.960 --> 33:28.180
a caged rabbit.

33:28.267 --> 33:32.053
You see, that is what
we do for each other.

33:32.140 --> 33:33.837
Come.

33:35.839 --> 33:38.407
I have something
to discuss with Delphine.

33:47.199 --> 33:48.548
Delphine.

33:48.635 --> 33:51.159
Come sit with me.

33:56.338 --> 33:57.905
Mr. Cooke.

33:57.992 --> 34:00.168
What are your impressions
of him?

34:01.691 --> 34:03.345
You said his stock
had lowered in town.

34:03.432 --> 34:06.261
Yes.

34:06.348 --> 34:08.350
And so has yours.

34:08.437 --> 34:11.875
A match could be of value
to the both of you.

34:11.962 --> 34:14.052
A French wife

34:14.139 --> 34:16.228
could remove the English stain.

34:18.099 --> 34:20.275
I've not asked
to be matched with Mr. Cooke.

34:20.362 --> 34:22.103
Or any man.

34:22.190 --> 34:24.845
I do believe there is
a tenderness inside of him.

34:24.932 --> 34:26.499
And he is a widower,

34:26.586 --> 34:28.457
which, in my experience,

34:28.544 --> 34:30.372
mellows a man.

34:33.114 --> 34:35.377
I shall think on it.

34:54.918 --> 34:56.920
♪ ♪

35:16.810 --> 35:18.768
♪ ♪

35:32.260 --> 35:34.393
MARI:
Come.

35:36.482 --> 35:38.440
When is the celebration?

35:42.575 --> 35:45.926
I don't know.

35:46.013 --> 35:49.582
You don't know
or you won't tell me?

35:51.366 --> 35:53.325
[exhales]

35:55.414 --> 35:57.329
That is the truth, Mari.

35:57.416 --> 35:59.331
I don't know.

35:59.418 --> 36:02.464
You are loyal to him.

36:02.551 --> 36:04.510
I understand.

36:12.474 --> 36:14.389
He saved my life.

36:14.476 --> 36:16.652
TREPAGNY [in distance]:
Mari?

36:16.739 --> 36:18.088
I should...

36:33.321 --> 36:35.280
What is this?

36:39.675 --> 36:41.764
Monsieur Sel?

36:42.852 --> 36:45.377
Um...

36:45.464 --> 36:47.422
supper.

36:49.119 --> 36:50.991
Do not take me for a fool.

36:51.078 --> 36:53.298
I can see it is supper.

36:55.430 --> 36:58.433
I will remind you
the greatest betrayal in history

36:58.520 --> 37:00.479
happened at a supper.

37:02.524 --> 37:04.526
Now what is this?

37:04.613 --> 37:06.659
MARI:
Go.

37:10.576 --> 37:12.186
Go on.

37:23.328 --> 37:25.286
What are you doing here?

37:28.376 --> 37:31.205
It is my home.

38:00.800 --> 38:02.628
Please.

38:09.983 --> 38:12.333
GAY BILL:
No personal failure
in an enterprise

38:12.420 --> 38:15.336
could make them consent

38:15.423 --> 38:18.078
to deprive their nation
of their valor.

38:18.165 --> 38:20.385
But they laid it at her feet

38:20.472 --> 38:23.170
as the most glorious
contribution they could offer.

38:23.257 --> 38:25.520
Gay Bill.

38:25.607 --> 38:27.392
That's Mr. Selby to you, Hamish.

38:27.479 --> 38:29.437
Such a grand fire in the woods
with the Iroquois about.

38:29.524 --> 38:31.744
Smoke for miles.

38:31.831 --> 38:33.963
Luckily, it is only me

38:34.050 --> 38:36.052
who has followed his snout
to your camp.

38:37.315 --> 38:39.099
Beans.

38:39.186 --> 38:42.624
I see the company's provisions
are still shit-all.

38:44.017 --> 38:46.367
I was told by Mr. Cooke

38:46.454 --> 38:49.675
that you have
the elusive Mr. Cross...

38:49.762 --> 38:51.894
who, in turn, has my pistols.

38:54.070 --> 38:56.072
Is he off in the woods,
vacating the beans?

38:57.987 --> 38:59.511
No.

38:59.598 --> 39:01.077
He's gone.

39:01.164 --> 39:03.863
How's that?

39:05.604 --> 39:07.780
Run off.
Deserted.

39:09.434 --> 39:10.652
Kept a loose rein on him?

39:10.739 --> 39:11.871
Perhaps.

39:14.787 --> 39:16.658
Bastard had my pistols.

39:16.745 --> 39:18.399
He threw them in the river.

39:18.486 --> 39:20.575
[snorts]

39:20.662 --> 39:22.185
Well, this has turned into

39:22.272 --> 39:25.058
a right mound of bear shit.

39:25.145 --> 39:27.147
You see, I have Iroquois

39:27.234 --> 39:29.149
keen to move against the French,

39:29.236 --> 39:31.238
but they want pistols,
and as you said,

39:31.325 --> 39:32.544
they're at the bottom
of the river.

39:32.631 --> 39:34.676
We spoke to Captain Wale
in Quebec City.

39:34.763 --> 39:36.635
[laughs]

39:38.463 --> 39:41.291
Ah, a right stiff tosser,
that one.

39:41.379 --> 39:43.859
Always on about
the grand agitating plan,

39:43.946 --> 39:46.122
how we should get the...
the French and the Iroquois

39:46.209 --> 39:48.124
to go at each other
like bees in a bottle.

39:48.211 --> 39:50.605
We know the plan.

39:56.655 --> 39:58.134
Good, then.

40:01.703 --> 40:03.575
Pointing the Iroquois
requires a...

40:03.662 --> 40:05.925
a strong belly.

40:06.012 --> 40:07.840
Are you the sort

40:07.927 --> 40:10.408
to flinch when the work
turns red?

40:17.893 --> 40:20.156
All right.

40:23.029 --> 40:24.770
Good, then.

40:24.857 --> 40:27.076
Let's put a skip to it.

40:45.051 --> 40:47.053
♪ ♪

40:59.892 --> 41:03.635
May the Holy Spirit fill
our steps with protection

41:03.722 --> 41:05.898
and bind our deeds and thoughts

41:05.985 --> 41:08.074
in his everlasting wisdom.

41:08.161 --> 41:10.685
Amen.

41:13.862 --> 41:16.604
You may go and hide,
if you like.

41:18.780 --> 41:20.042
No, Mother,

41:20.129 --> 41:23.959
we will do no such thing.

41:24.046 --> 41:26.701
Then I ask that you stay
with the soldiers.

41:26.788 --> 41:29.269
We will go forth
and take the bodies.

41:29.356 --> 41:31.793
It is better that the Iroquois
see only us

41:31.880 --> 41:34.666
and not men with guns
and schemes. Do you agree?

41:34.753 --> 41:37.538
Well, we shall obey
your infinite wisdom.

41:37.625 --> 41:40.106
May God guide your steps.

41:42.935 --> 41:45.633
SABRINE:
♪ Yea, though I walk♪

41:45.720 --> 41:49.071
♪ Through the valley
of the shadow of death♪

41:49.158 --> 41:52.074
♪ I will fear no evil♪

41:53.554 --> 41:56.992
♪ For thou art with me.♪

42:08.395 --> 42:10.571
Why have you brought us here?

42:10.658 --> 42:13.269
I thought it best
you see the endgame now.

42:13.356 --> 42:16.446
I misjudged Mr. Cross.

42:16.534 --> 42:18.536
I have no intention
of doing the same with you.

42:18.623 --> 42:19.798
Where's their chief?

42:19.885 --> 42:22.409
Chief Tehonikonhraken.

42:22.496 --> 42:24.977
He's a cautious man,
but he's taken his son's advice

42:25.064 --> 42:26.456
as to how the region
should be managed.

42:26.544 --> 42:28.458
And how is that?

42:28.546 --> 42:31.374
Ratahsénthos.
He'd hop the walls of Wobik

42:31.461 --> 42:33.115
and tomahawk every French
if I told him.

42:33.202 --> 42:34.160
And you can manage him?

42:35.509 --> 42:36.989
As much as his father can.

42:39.513 --> 42:41.820
Chief Tehonikonhraken.

42:43.343 --> 42:45.650
These men are
Hudson's Bay men.

42:45.737 --> 42:48.130
They have many uses.

43:38.050 --> 43:40.226
-GAY BILL: Let's go.
-[man calling out in Mohawk]

43:55.154 --> 43:57.547
I want no part of this.

43:57.635 --> 44:01.116
What would you have us do, Yvon?
Run? Stop them?

44:01.203 --> 44:03.771
-No.
-What, then?

44:03.858 --> 44:05.730
Wait?

44:05.817 --> 44:07.427
Watch?

44:07.514 --> 44:09.777
The result will be the same.

44:09.864 --> 44:12.084
A skin for a skin.

44:12.171 --> 44:15.130
I have done my time in hell
for the Company.

44:15.217 --> 44:17.785
Go, if you want.

44:17.872 --> 44:19.613
I will not think less of you.

44:19.700 --> 44:22.007
Scout says the French
are almost here.

44:22.094 --> 44:25.488
With nuns in front.

44:25.575 --> 44:27.577
Now, that's some
crafty thinking.

44:27.665 --> 44:30.058
I wish to have the plan.

44:30.145 --> 44:32.017
The plan is we outflank them,

44:32.104 --> 44:34.193
pick off the soldiers
one by one.

44:34.280 --> 44:37.109
They're the Intendant's men,
most likely.

44:37.196 --> 44:39.459
The chief thinks they'll
pretty up the tree.

44:39.546 --> 44:41.243
I don't disagree.

44:41.330 --> 44:43.115
And the nuns?

44:43.202 --> 44:45.160
We'll get to that part later.

44:47.554 --> 44:48.903
We'll go with you.

44:57.782 --> 44:59.522
Go, if you wish.

45:02.700 --> 45:04.614
Oh, hell.

45:07.313 --> 45:10.272
SABRINE:
♪ To lie down♪

45:10.359 --> 45:12.797
♪ In green pastures♪

45:12.884 --> 45:15.364
♪ He restoreth my soul...♪

45:18.367 --> 45:20.326
Let 'em pass.

45:38.126 --> 45:39.649
We will die here.

45:39.737 --> 45:42.652
Yes, we might well.

45:51.357 --> 45:52.662
Stay close.

45:52.750 --> 45:54.360
-Don't go too far.
-[gunshot]

46:10.419 --> 46:11.856
♪ ♪

46:23.041 --> 46:24.607
[grunting]

46:24.694 --> 46:26.914
[Gay Bill laughing]

46:27.001 --> 46:29.961
You see, now there's
some cleverness.

46:30.048 --> 46:32.050
-An Englishman.
-I will not

46:32.137 --> 46:33.921
draw my pistol.
I am no duelist.

46:35.096 --> 46:36.794
That's a fair assessment.

46:41.102 --> 46:42.190
Please.

46:42.277 --> 46:43.539
He is with me.

46:45.933 --> 46:47.543
I found some friends of yours.

46:49.894 --> 46:52.200
I don't suppose
you have my pistols?

46:53.332 --> 46:55.160
I do not.

46:55.247 --> 46:58.293
I can p-procure more
if you release my man

46:58.380 --> 47:01.253
and let the sisters
collect the dead.

47:03.646 --> 47:05.387
Your man.

47:07.868 --> 47:09.435
Yes.

47:09.522 --> 47:13.004
The nuns?
That's in God's hands.

47:13.091 --> 47:15.136
Or should I say
Chief Tehonikonhraken's.

47:15.223 --> 47:17.486
Which is a... a coin toss.

47:17.573 --> 47:19.053
Good.
Good, good.

47:19.140 --> 47:21.273
Uh, then allow us to walk.

47:21.360 --> 47:23.144
Uh, we will return the bodies.

47:23.231 --> 47:24.972
My good name will be restored
with the heroics.

47:25.059 --> 47:26.887
The eye of scrutiny
will be lifted.

47:26.974 --> 47:29.281
Then you will ha-have your guns.

47:43.773 --> 47:45.993
Kirkwall is...

47:46.080 --> 47:48.474
very lovely in the spring...

47:50.084 --> 47:51.999
...when the heather is out.

47:52.086 --> 47:55.307
The light on the church stones.

47:57.787 --> 47:59.833
Do you remember it?

48:01.922 --> 48:05.534
It says much about a man
to hail from such a place.

48:08.973 --> 48:10.409
What's he on about?

48:10.496 --> 48:12.585
We are, all of us,

48:12.672 --> 48:15.414
of the same kingdom.

48:15.501 --> 48:18.765
Pistols for the dead.

48:18.852 --> 48:22.160
A toss of a coin for the nuns.

48:23.639 --> 48:25.119
That's my offer.

48:27.556 --> 48:29.167
SABRINE:
♪ The Lord is my shepherd♪

48:29.254 --> 48:32.039
♪ I shall not want♪

48:32.126 --> 48:34.128
♪ He leadeth me♪

48:34.215 --> 48:37.871
♪ Beside the still waters♪

48:37.958 --> 48:41.614
♪ He restoreth my soul♪

48:41.701 --> 48:44.138
♪ He leadeth me♪

48:44.225 --> 48:48.012
♪ To the path of righteous...♪

48:57.935 --> 48:59.937
♪ Yea, though I walk
through the valley♪

49:00.024 --> 49:03.244
♪ Of the shadow of death♪

49:03.331 --> 49:06.421
-[indistinct praying]
-♪ I will fear no evil♪

49:08.641 --> 49:11.861
♪ For Thou art with me♪

49:17.215 --> 49:20.609
♪ In the presence
of mine enemies♪

49:22.481 --> 49:26.267
